The strings `-Dloader.main=com.xxx.globalpayments.feeds.downstream.DownstreamDataFactoryApplication` and `org.springframework.boot.loader.PropertiesLauncher` are passed to `main` as command line parameters. They aren&#39;t interpreted by `java` or Spring Boot.

The correct command line is:
```
java -Dloader.main=com.example.demo.DemoApplication3 \
  -cp target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar \
  org.springframework.boot.loader.PropertiesLauncher
```
assuming that your application class is `com.example.demo.DemoApplication3`

